SCRUPULOUS ALIGNMENT

Scrupulous is the alignment of heroes who will bend the rules for the greater
good, but never become the villain they fight.

A Scrupulous character has a strong sense of right and wrong and dislikes
lies and deception.  They prefer to work within the law but will break it
when they must to protect the innocent or stop a greater evil.  They keep
their word to good and neutral characters, and may or may not keep it with
evil ones if breaking it would save lives.

GUIDELINES:
- Prefers to tell the truth but will lie when lives depend on it
- Will break the law only when it serves the greater good
- Will not harm innocents; reluctant to harm even enemies who surrender
- Will keep promises to good and neutral beings
- Will use force proportional to the threat
- Uncomfortable working with evil characters, but will do so if necessary

Scrupulous characters represent the pragmatic heroes of Rifts: the Ley Line
Walker who breaks Coalition curfew to rescue prisoners, the Wilderness Scout
who shelters wanted refugees.  They are the most common alignment among
adventurers because they can work in a morally complex world without losing
their soul.

They are trusted by most good characters and seen as reliable by neutrals.
Evil characters know they can never be pushed into truly villainous acts.

See also: principled, unprincipled, anarchist, miscreant, aberrant, diabolic
